Actress Heather Locklear was arrested for driving under the effect of an unknown drug.
The actress Heather Locklear, who is known for her role as Amanda in the series "Melrose Place", was arrested this weekend in Santa Barbara (California) for driving under the effect of an unknown drug.
A witness has observed how she tried to leave her parking space in Montecito in a rather strange way, reported spokesman of the traffic police of California to the magazine 'People'.
The witness detailed that Locklear 'pushed the gas pedal after 4: 30 p.m. and made a lot of noise by trying to move her car out of the parking space to the rear or the front, and as she drove backwards she grabbed her sunglasses several times'.
A little later the witness, who had probably not known the actress at the beginning, saw that Locklear stopped on a nearby street and got out of the car.
The witness was the person who notified the Emergency Service because she 'was afraid to live Locklears'.
When the police patrol arrived, they found the actress sitting in her car, which stood across the street, blocking traffic.
'She seemed to be disoriented ', so they took the police to a special drug and alcohol centre to do a test.
According to a police spokesperson, the actress was cooperative, excessive alcohol consumption was excluded from the first moment. 'According to the first observations of the officials, we believe that Locklear was under the influence of an unknown drug,' said the speaker.
Locklear was arrested on suspicion of driving under the influence of an indefinite substance, which could not be determined, and taken to a local detention centre at around 7 p.m.
Two months ago, Locklaer was discharged from the Arizona clinic after receiving treatment for anxiety and depression.
