The total contribution of 15 million made by the Autonomous Community of Madrid for filming offers Garci, as he added, the 'unique opportunity' to portray, with the help of decorations and appropriate clothing, the image of 'confused Spain, which chose the false leader for the fight, because the people had been put behind by the fight for independence and under the rule of Ferdinand the VII'.
