Talking in your sleep
Some children speak at night
I am not talking about those who wake up and tell us something about what happened the day before, but about the children who speak while they are asleep.
When it happens to you for the first time, at best you will be frightened, but in reality it doesn't matter.
This is a positive sleep disorder called speaking in sleep.
It is quite widespread, especially among children and young people.
Certainly, more than one of you has been told that you spoke at night.
This phenomenon can occur occasionally (once in a lifetime, for example, during a high fever), or regularly (every day, once a week, once a month), the next day the child cannot remember anything.
There is no reason for this phenomenon.
Often connections are sought with other phenomena in sleep, such as nightmares, panic fear at night, enuresis noctura (bedwetting at night), speaking in sleep, but there is no reason for this.
As we have mentioned before, it can be due to very high fibers, stressful situations or excessive demands.
In any case, this is a little researched phenomenon.
The frequency with which it occurs is very variable.
It can be that one speaks calmly in single words, whispers or it can be quite the opposite (screams, crying, long discussions).
In cases where the expression is very intense, it is recommended to observe the child and seek advice from a specialist in order to check whether there is a problem that causes anxiety and in this way comes about.
We have said that it is a positive disorder, so it is not treated, either, it is associated with another sleep disorder that can be treated (for example, with sleep, apnea or with the stress).
What you can do is to perform a series of simple preventive actions:
Try not to excite the child before sleeping.
So, choose quiet game for the child and avoid stressful TV programs that are terrible and a bit too wild.
For the nervous children to whom relaxation is recommended, relaxation methods can be used to help them to get a certain inner peace.
This helps the child to sleep calmly.
When speech occurs in sleep, try to keep calm.
Remember that it is harmless for the child and the next day it will not remember anything that happened.
Useful advice
Don't wake it up.
This is useless, for the child is unconscious, so you will tear him out of sleep.
Although the child is speaking, he is sleeping, so he is resting.
Think about it, if it appears to be frightened after a couple, then it is recommended to seek advice or find out what reason the child has for the fear.
When they understand what it says (which is not so common), they don't put pressure on the child to make an interrogation and get more information.
So you won't be able to achieve anything with it, because when the child is asleep, it is unconscious and can't think about it.
Also, you will hear what it says, but you will not know what it dreams and why it says so, so be careful with the interpretation of the information and the conclusions you draw from it.
Maybe, it doesn't tell the child that you hear it at night and know its secrets.
Not even as a joke.
This causes a lot of fear.
So, don ’ t worry, it ’ s not bad, it ’ s a moment that only takes a few minutes.
