The opposition fears that the Organisation for Security and Cooperation in Europe, which followed the electoral process, does not recognise the election as valid.
It stresses that voter turnout seems too high and that the extension of the vote in advance (26% of the Minsk electorate) has paved the way for any kind of manipulation.
'Did you notice that an election took place? 'asks Social Democrat leader Alexander Kozulin, one of the last two political prisoners released in August of this year.
